Place one secret per file (no trailing newline).

Required files for docker-compose secrets:
  alpaca_api_key       — Alpaca API key
  alpaca_secret_key    — Alpaca secret key
  polygon_api_key      — Polygon API key for intraday market/news data
  smtp_password        — Gmail app password for alert emails

Example:
  echo -n "PKXXXXXXXX" > secrets/alpaca_api_key
  echo -n "SKXXXXXXXX" > secrets/alpaca_secret_key
  echo -n "pgXXXXXXX"  > secrets/polygon_api_key
  echo -n "app-pass"   > secrets/smtp_password

These files are bind-mounted to /run/secrets/<name> inside containers.
The application reads from the file first, falling back to the
corresponding environment variable (ALPACA_API_KEY, etc.).
